<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,159,255]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">
Note that the epithet “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Raymond-Hamet" authorityYear="1941" box="[424,505,160,183]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="4" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stearnii">
<emphasis box="[424,505,160,183]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">stearnii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” is misspelt “ 
<emphasis box="[656,733,160,183]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">steamii</emphasis>
” in the online catalogue of Herb. P. Further, as part of the metadata held for this specimen in the online catalogue of Herb. P it is noted as originating from “Tropical Africa”. However, there is no indication on the specimen itself that it originated from that region.
</paragraph>
